subject: Automate 7 testcase to verify BIOS attributes using redfish
commitMessage:
Automate 7 testcase to verify BIOS attributes using redfish

          - Redfish Verify Set BIOS Integer Attribute Type
          - Redfish Verify Set BIOS String Attribute Type
          - Redfish Verify Set BIOS Attribute With Invalid Attribute Name
          - Redfish Verify Set Invalid Optional Value For BIOS Enumeration Attribute Type
          - Redfish Verify Set Out Of Range Integer Value For BIOS Integer Attribute Type
          - Redfish Verify Set Out Of Range String Value For BIOS String Attribute Type
          - Redfish Verify Restore BIOS Attribute Values

Change-Id: I660b32341d17022db46a1c364fb9436d52b5f603
Signed-off-by: Sridevi Ramesh <sridevra@in.ibm.com>

we need automation for this stuff:
- we need to set all the enum, string,integer attributes and check if the attributes reflect the same.
- we need to set all the possible values for an enum,string,integer attributes to see if they are - being set or not. and also check out of possible values.
- we need to set out-of-range values for string / integer attributes and check if we are returning a proper error.

> And all the above we need to do for both host on & host off case. I am not sure if this is done as part of this commit.
> we also need to test the bad cases , which also seemed to be missing in this commit.
